cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.RO 

The paper discusses Particle Swarm Optimization (PSO), which is a metaheuristic optimization algorithm commonly used in the field of computational intelligence. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of PSO in unsupervised, complex multidimensional problems, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of PSO in optimization problems, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.RO (Robotics).
